Of course, for friendship to have an effect, it must first of all be accessible.
In this age of communication dominated by social networks, where the emphasis is on style and not substance, the immediate nature of the response often takes precedence over meaningful contact.
Our digital lives have doubled the need to create the appearance of a strong personality, open to fun and success, even if in reality it is isolation that dominates.
