According to Mediafax, there were 290 votes "for" and 108 "against".
The vote was secret, with ballot papers.
The PNL representatives were the only ones who voted against this proposal, Digi24 informs.
Moreover, the liberals criticized Sarbu’s appointment to this position and announced that they will challenge it to the CCR, provided that he has a DNA file, but does not have the necessary training and experience.
Ilie Sarbu has 30 days, according to the law, to resign from the Senate, because the new function of the Court of Auditors does not allow him to do politics.
The PSD senator will serve as vice-president of the Audit Authority of the Court of Auditors, which remained free after Ioan Anton was revoked, following a decision of the Constitutional Court in September 2014, which found that he was appointed unconstitutional.
